nit, we use 'depth-first-method-ordering'. I'm not sure if it's always the cleanest for tests. The ordering essentially is that methods should be defined as soon after first usage as possible. IE:
@Test
void foo() {
  helper1();
  helper2();
  // stuff
}

void helper1() { ... }

void helper2() { ... }

@Test
void foo2() {
   helper1();
   helper2();
  :
  :
}

