timeline.bodyText:
We're trying to kill Tuple, please avoid it's usage. Typically we recommend to just use a value object instead. Lombok makes this pretty easy. EG:
@Value
class MustFightBattleWithExecutable {
  private MustFightBattle mustFightBattle;
  private IExecutable executable;
}

Second, the usage is quite hard to follow, ie:
  givenFirstStrikeBattleSetup(true, true, true, true, true),

Do you have any object to extracting the parameters to a value object?
EG:
givenBattleSetup(BattleSetupParameters.builder()
   .firstStrike(true)
   .attackerHasDestroyer(true)
   .defenderHasDestroyer(true)
   .ww2v2Rules(true)
   .build());

One nice benefit here is that any booleans that are false can be omitted and you can use the default 'false' value for them.

