CONSIDER THIS COMMENT FIRST!
After reading through most of the tests, the pattern of testing I think has become more clear. Have you considered parameterizing the whole thing?
If you had a value object for the battle setup, then it should become pretty easy!
Example:
@ParameterizedTest
@MethodSource
void verifyFirstStrikeBattleScenarios( 
     BattleSetupParameters setup, MustFightBattle returnFire, boolean attackersExpectedToHaveFirstStrike) {

   verifyFirstStrikebattle(
        setup,  returnFire,  attackersExpectedToHaveFirstStrike);
}


static List<Arguments> verifyFirstStrikeBattleScenarios() {
  return List.of(
     Arguments.of(BattleSetupParameters.builder()....build(), MustFightBattle.ReturnFire.ALL, false),
     :
     :
     );
}

